Malaysia and Indonesia both claim sovereignty over the Celebes Sea islands.
The island restricts access to 80 divers and 40 staff to protect the coral reef.
Sipadan, a top diving spot, is off the coast of Sabah, Malaysia.
The recent abduction of 20 hostages by armed men has sparked a search operation.
The hostages, including foreign tourists, were taken from a Malaysian diving resort.
Malaysian and Philippine authorities are working together to track down the kidnappers.
The hostages include tourists from France, Germany, the United States, and South Africa.
The situation remains tense as efforts are made to secure their release.
